The paper deals with collapse results in database theory, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under cs.DB. The paper also involves linearly ordered context structures, which is a topic in cs.LO (computational logic). The use of Ehrenfeucht-Fraisse games suggests a connection to model theory, which falls under cs.LO and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also involves the construction of winning strategies, which is a topic in cs.CC (computational complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the spectra of FO(<,+)-sentences, which is a topic in cs.DS (data structures and algorithms).
